<p>Indian CAs deal with a unique mix of work, statutory compliance, audit documentation, GST filing, client advisory, that involves large volumes of text and numbers. AI tools have started to genuinely help with the document-heavy parts: drafting communication, summarising reports, looking up tax sections, generating templates. The numerical work (audit calculations, return filing) still belongs in your existing software.</p>

<p>This guide covers what is worth paying for in 2026 and what to avoid.</p>

<h2>Where AI helps a CA practice</h2>

<p><strong>High value:</strong> drafting client emails and follow-ups, summarising long audit reports and clauses, generating engagement letter drafts, looking up GST and Income Tax sections (with verification), creating client-facing explainers, drafting notice replies.</p>

<p><strong>Avoid:</strong> blindly trusting AI for tax computation, deduction eligibility decisions, or filing-related calculations. Always verify against the latest CBDT circular or GSTN guidance.</p>

<h2>The 3 AI tools we recommend for Indian CAs</h2>

<h3>Claude Pro, for client communication and audit summaries</h3>
<div class="tool-card">
  <span class="price-tag">Free tier (limited)</span>
  <span class="price-tag">Pro: &#8377;2,005/month with GST</span>
  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Drafting client letters, follow-up emails, engagement letters, summarising long audit reports, simplifying GST/IT sections for clients, drafting replies to scrutiny notices and responses to queries.</p>
  <p><strong>Why CAs prefer it:</strong> Claude's privacy default (no training on chats, on the Pro plan) is the strongest of the major AI tools. Long-form output is more accurate than ChatGPT's, important when summarising 80-page audit reports. The free tier is good enough to test before paying.</p>
