<h2>Privacy and client data</h2>

<p>Client financial data is sensitive. The CA Act and ICAI ethics expect confidentiality. Practical rules for cloud AI:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Never paste real client names, PAN, GSTIN, or account numbers into AI tools.</li>
  <li>Use the paid Pro tier of Claude or ChatGPT (privacy default is stronger; no training on your chats).</li>
  <li>For tax research and section lookups, full pasting of published sections is fine.</li>
  <li>For client-specific advisory, write the question in generic terms ("a private limited company in the manufacturing sector with FY 2024-25 turnover of approximately X").</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to pay for AI tools as a CA in India</h2>

<p>For firm-level subscriptions, ask your office to expense it. For personal subscriptions, use a forex card or Niyo Global (regular Indian debit cards are often rejected). Notion accepts UPI directly so it is the simplest payment-wise. Full payment guide: <a href="/guides/pay-for-ai-tools-india/">5 ways to pay for AI tools from India</a>.</p>

<p>The subscription is a deductible expense for your practice; save the GST invoice from the provider's billing dashboard.</p>

